    13|
    14|    /**
    15|     * Returns true when this tool only reads state and never mutates the workspace.
    16|     * Read-only tools can be dispatched in parallel within a single agent loop iteration.
    17|     */
    18|    default boolean isReadOnly() {
    19|        return false;
    20|    }
    21|
    22|    /**
    23|     * Returns true when this tool has irreversible side effects on external persistent state
    24|     * (e.g. file writes, job submissions, third-party system mutations). Destructive tools are
    25|     * always run serially and generate a WARN-level log entry on each invocation.
    26|     *
    27|     * <p>A tool that returns {@code true} here must also return {@code false} from
    28|     * {@link #isReadOnly()}; the two flags are mutually exclusive.
    29|     *
    30|     * <p>Future: check this flag inside {@link #isAuthorized} to enforce a blocking gate for
    31|     * strict read-only execution modes.
    32|     */
    33|    default boolean isDestructive() {
    34|        return false;
    35|    }
    36|
    37|    /**
    38|     * Authorization gate called by the agent loop before every tool execution.
    39|     *
    40|     * <p>Returns {@code true} if this tool is permitted to execute in the given workspace
    41|     * context. The default implementation always permits execution — override this method
    42|     * in write-capable tools to enforce additional restrictions such as read-only workspace
    43|     * mode, user-level permission checks, or environment guards.
    44|     *
    45|     * <p>When this method returns {@code false}, the agent loop returns an
    46|     * {@code "UNAUTHORIZED"} error string to Claude instead of calling
    47|     * {@link #execute(WorkspaceContext, java.util.Map)}, providing a defence-in-depth
    48|     * layer independent of the {@code ToolDefinitions} mode that was used to build the
    49|     * tool list.
    50|     *
    51|     * @param workspace the current workspace context; may be {@code null} in chat mode
    52|     * @return {@code true} to allow execution; {@code false} to block it
    53|     */
    54|    default boolean isAuthorized(WorkspaceContext workspace) {
    55|        return true;
